// REST manual tests for TUC 2: Track Bus in Real-Time (TrackBus)
// Base URL: http://localhost:8080
//
// Notes:
// 1) Assumption from UC: Member is logged in.
// 2) Most /transit endpoints are public, but /map/config requires auth.
// 3) Replace placeholder tokens/route IDs where needed.

// ============================================================================
// BASIC FLOW (TUC2)
// ============================================================================

// Step 1: Member selects a route from filter.
// Expected: 200 OK, RoutesRetrieved
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/routes?system=PRT
###

// Pick a routeId from the previous response (example: P1).
// Step 2/5: App requests route coordinates/patterns for selected route.
// Expected: 200 OK, PathGenerated
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/routes/P1
###

// Step 2/5: App requests current vehicle locations for selected route.
// Expected: 200 OK, VehiclesLocated
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/vehicles/P1
###

// Optional: Fetch stops to support map stop interactions.
// Expected: 200 OK, StopsRetrieved
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/stops/P1?dir=INBOUND
###

// Optional: Fetch predictions for a known stop (replace stopId as needed).
// Expected: 200 OK, PredictionsRetrieved
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/stops/7079/predictions
###

// Step 8 + Rule R2/R4 (30s refresh + freshness):
// Run this request twice with ~30 seconds between runs.
// Expected: both calls 200; payload may change; timestamps should be recent.
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/vehicles/P1
###

// Wait ~30 seconds, then run again and compare:
// - vehicle lat/lon and/or heading may update
// - lastUpdate should not be stale beyond refresh expectations
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/vehicles/P1
###

// ============================================================================
// RULE VALIDATION
// ============================================================================

// R1 Selected Routes: only vehicles for selected route should be returned.
// Expected: every payload item has routeId == P1
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/vehicles/P1
###

// Optional cross-check against a different route (example G2).
// Expected: payload routeIds should be G2 only.
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/vehicles/G2
###

// ============================================================================
// ALTERNATIVE FLOWS
// ============================================================================

// A1 Reroute: route has active detour event.
// Expected: 200 OK, DetoursRetrieved. If payload not empty, route is detoured.
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/detours/P1
###

// A1 Reroute geometry: detour path data used for map rendering.
// Expected: 200 OK, DetoursRetrieved; payload geometry may include detourPath/originalPath.
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/detours/P1/geometry
###

// A2 No Data Available: no active vehicles for route.
// Expected: 200 OK, VehiclesLocated with [] payload for inactive/unknown route.
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/vehicles/NO_ACTIVE_ROUTE
###

// A3 API Connection Failure (Google Maps):
// Server-side HTTP check here is map config availability; map rendering failure is client-side.
// Expected: 401 MissingToken when auth missing (confirms frontend would fail map bootstrap).
GET http://localhost:8080/map/config
###

// A4 System Busy / Upstream unavailable:
// Check health endpoint for degraded upstream status.
// Expected: 200 with status object; if upstream down/rate-limited, overall can become false.
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/health
###

// A5 TrueTime substitution with CMU Shuttle (Tripshot):
// 1) Get CMU routes.
// Expected: 200 OK, RoutesRetrieved (payload includes route IDs like CMU-*) when configured.
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/routes?system=CMU
###

// 2) Replace <CMU_ROUTE_ID> with an ID from previous response.
// Expected: 200 OK, VehiclesLocated
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/vehicles/<CMU_ROUTE_ID>
###

// 3) Replace <CMU_ROUTE_ID> and direction.
// Expected: 200 OK, StopsRetrieved (or 404 if no configured data for route/direction).
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/stops/<CMU_ROUTE_ID>?dir=OUTBOUND
###

// ============================================================================
// ERROR HANDLING CHECKS (useful for manual robustness checks)
// ============================================================================

// Missing required query parameter dir.
// Expected: 400 MissingParameter
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/stops/P1
###

// Unknown route patterns.
// Expected: 404 RouteNotFound
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/routes/INVALID_ROUTE
###

// Unknown stop predictions.
// Expected: 404 StopNotFound OR 200 with [] depending upstream feed state.
GET http://localhost:8080/transit/stops/99999/predictions
###
